{"title_page": "Focus (Ariana Grande song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Focus\n| cover      = Focus cover art.png\n| alt        = A picture showing a woman in a purple background with her arms through her body, her long ponytailed, platinum hair falls over her right shoulder. She wears a white mini skirt and a top.\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Ariana Grande]]\n| album      = [[Dangerous Woman]] (Japanese version)\n| released   = {{Start date|2015|10|30}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single]]|[[Music download|digital download]]}}\n| recorded   = 2015 {{hlist|[[MXM Studios]]<br />{{small|(Los Angeles, California)}}|[[Wolf Cousins Studios]]<br />{{small|(Stockholm, Sweden)}}}}\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=31}}\n| label      = [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Savan Kotecha]]|[[Peter Svensson]]|[[Max Martin]]|[[Ilya Salmanzadeh]]|Ariana Grande}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|Max Martin|Ilya}}\n| prev_title = [[E Pi\u00f9 Ti Penso]]\n| prev_year  = 2015\n| next_title = [[Boys Like You (Who Is Fancy song)|Boys Like You]]\n| next_year  = 2015\n| misc       = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|lf_wVfwpfp8|\"Focus\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Focus'''\" is a song recorded by American singer [[Ariana Grande]]. It was released on October 30, 2015 by [[Republic Records]], and was originally intended to be the opening track as well as the lead single off Grande's third studio album, ''[[Dangerous Woman]]'' (then called ''Moonlight''). \"[[Dangerous Woman (song)|Dangerous Woman]]\" replaced it as the lead single, and the song was later scrapped from the standard-edition track listing, however it was included as a bonus track on the album's Japanese version. The song was written by Grande, [[Savan Kotecha]], [[Peter Svensson]] and its producers, [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]] and [[Max Martin]]. \"Focus\" features [[horn (instrument)|horns]] ([[saxophone]], [[trumpet]] and [[trombone]]), with cowbells and handclaps as percussion.\n\nThe song received generally mixed reviews from [[Music journalism|music critics]]. Some praised Grande's vocals and the song's brassy production, and others criticized its similarity to her 2014 song \"[[Problem (song)|Problem]]\". \"Focus\" debuted at number seven on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], with 113,000 downloads in its first week. It was Grande's sixth top-ten single, and her first unaccompanied by another artist. The song also reached the top ten in Canada, Australia, Greece, Italy, Spain and the United Kingdom. By January 2016, \"Focus\" sold 544,000 copies in the United States and was certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]].\n\nIts music video, directed by [[Hannah Lux Davis]], premiered on October 30, 2015 on Grande's [[Vevo]] channel. She performed \"Focus\" at the November 22 [[2015 American Music Awards]] and at the [[iHeartRadio]] Theater Los Angeles concert, and it was on the set list of the second leg of Grande's 2017 [[Dangerous Woman Tour]].\n\n==Background and release==\n\"Focus\" was written by Grande, [[Savan Kotecha]], Peter Svensson and its producers, [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]] and [[Max Martin]].<ref name=\"credits\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/focus-mw0002894390/credits|title=Focus &#91;Single&#93;|publisher=[[AllMusic]]. [[Rovi Corporation]]|accessdate=July 6, 2017}}</ref> Serban Ghenea mixed the song, aided by John Hands.<ref name=\"Notes\">{{cite AV media notes|title=Focus|type=CD liner notes|others=[[Ariana Grande]]|publisher=[[Republic Records]]|year=2015}}</ref> Grande began working on a new material for her third studio album in May 2015, posting details about the project on social media and in conversations with the public. The album was originally entitled ''Moonlight''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7594806/ariana-grande-moonlight-album-title|title= Ariana Grande Confirms Her New Album Is Titled ''Moonlight''|publisher= [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date= May 30, 2015|access-date= July 6, 2017|first= Christina|last= Lee}}</ref> The singer posted an unfocused picture of herself on her [[Instagram]] page in July 2015 with the caption \"Focus\", calling it a \"hint\". A video released in September 2015 by iHeartMedia Music Summit demonstrated that Grande, [[Republic Records]] CEO Monte Lipman and her manager, Charlie Walk, played the song to the approval of the Republic Records staff.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fuse.tv/2015/08/ariana-grande-new-song-focus-on-me|title=Ariana Grande Teases New Single \"Focus,\" Hear It Now!|publisher=[[Fuse (magazine)|Fuse]]|date= October 6, 2015|access-date= July 6, 2017|first= Jeff|last= Benjamin|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304005427/https://www.fuse.tv/2015/08/ariana-grande-new-song-focus-on-me|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nGrande announced the single during her September 15, 2015 appearance on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'', with a release date of October 30.<ref name=Goodman>{{cite journal| last=Goodman|first=Jessica|title=Ariana Grande announces new single, 'Focus'|journal=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|date=September 16, 2015| url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/16/ariana-grande-new-single-focus|accessdate=September 18, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304005526/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/16/ariana-grande-new-single-focus/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> She began posting snippets of the song's lyrics, video and audio previews and [[Pixelation|pixelated]] versions of the single's cover in early October on Instagram and [[Twitter]], and unveiled \"Focus{{\"'}} cover art on October 14. A week before the song's release date, A 15-second snippet of the track was used in a commercial for Ari by Ariana Grande, the singer's debut fragrance, a week before the song's release.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ariana Grande Teases 'Focus' In Debut Perfume Ad|url=http://www.fuse.tv/videos/2015/10/ariana-grande-focus-perfume-ad/|publisher=Fuse|date=October 20, 2015|access-date= March 3, 2018|first= Jeff|last= Benjamin|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304005836/https://www.fuse.tv/videos/2015/10/ariana-grande-focus-perfume-ad|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> \"Focus\" was [[Music download|digitally released]] worldwide on October 30, 2015, and was added to [[hot adult contemporary]] playlists in the United States on November 2.\n\n=== Removal from ''Dangerous Woman'' ===\nThe song was originally intended to be the lead single of Grande's third studio album, ''[[Dangerous Woman]]'' (then entitled ''Moonlight'').<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Reed|last=Ryan|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/hear-ariana-grandes-brash-brassy-new-song-focus-20151030|title= Hear Ariana Grande's Brash, Brassy New Song 'Focus'|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |date= October 30, 2015|access-date= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304010034/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/hear-ariana-grandes-brash-brassy-new-song-focus-20151030|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> Republic Records later told ''Billboard'' that the track had been removed from the album's standard edition, with \"[[Dangerous Woman (song)|Dangerous Woman]]\" replacing it as the lead single.<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Trust|last=Gary|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7263992/rihanna-hot-100-no-1-fifth-week-ariana-grande-debuts|title= Rihanna Rules Hot 100 for Fifth Week, Ariana Grande Debuts at No. 10|magazine= [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date= March 21, 2016|access-date= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304010219/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7263992/rihanna-hot-100-no-1-fifth-week-ariana-grande-debuts|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> However, the song is a bonus track on the album's Japanese version.<ref name=\"JPA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.universal-music.co.jp/ariana-grande/news/2016/03/23 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hgyx7b9X?url=http://www.universal-music.co.jp/ariana-grande/news/2016/03/23/ |archivedate=2016-05-22 |language=Japanese |trans-title=Miracle collaboration is seen! ! Japanese version MV of the hit single \"Focus!\" with \"Ariana Grande \u00d7 Rika-chan\" This is the first time Rika-chan appeared in the MV of an overseas artists! ! |script-title=ja:\u5947\u8de1\u306e\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\u30ec\u30fc\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u304c\u5b9f\u73fe\uff01\uff01\u300c\u30a2\u30ea\u30a2\u30ca\u30fb\u30b0\u30e9\u30f3\u30c7 \u00d7 \u30ea\u30ab\u3061\u3083\u3093\u300d\u30d2\u30c3\u30c8\u30fb\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u300c\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30ab\u30b9\u300d\u306e\u65e5\u672c\u7248\uff2d\uff36\u5b8c\u6210\uff01\u30ea\u30ab\u3061\u3083\u3093\u304c\u6d77\u5916\u30a2\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30b9\u30c8\u306e\uff2d\uff36\u306b\u51fa\u6f14\u3059\u308b\u306e\u306f\u521d\uff01\uff01 |publisher=[[Universal Music Japan]] |accessdate=May 10, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universal-music.co.jp/ariana-grande|language=Japanese|trans-title=\"Ariana Grande \u00d7 Rika-chan\" \"Focus\" music video|script-title=ja:\u30a2\u30ea\u30a2\u30ca\u30fb\u30b0\u30e9\u30f3\u30c7\u00d7\u30ea\u30ab\u3061\u3083\u3093\u300c\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30ab\u30b9\u300d\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30c3\u30af\u30fb\u30d3\u30c7\u30aa|publisher=[[Universal Music Japan]]|accessdate=May 10, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Vulture.com]]'' editor Dee Locket explained why \"Focus\" was not included on the album's final cut; the song's rollout was not \"remembered as a success \u2013 it was calculated to a fault, too polished for a time when pop\u2019s biggest stars, particularly its women, were letting their flaws bleed into the music.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vulture.com/2016/05/album-review-ariana-grande-dangerous-woman.html|title= With Dangerous Woman, Ariana Grande Shows That Being a Work in Progress Is Serving Her Well|work= [[Vulture (magazine)|Vulture]]|first= Dee|last= Lockett|date= May 27, 2016|access-date= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304010457/http://www.vulture.com/2016/05/album-review-ariana-grande-dangerous-woman.html|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Music and lyrics==\n[[File:Jamie Foxx by Gage Skidmore.jpg|alt=A smiling Jamie Foxx|thumb|upright|[[Jamie Foxx]] sings \"Focus{{\"'}} chorus.]]\nAccording to sheet music published by [[Kobalt Music]] on Musicnotes.com, \"Focus\" was written in the key of [[G-sharp minor|G{{Sharp}} minor]] and set in [[time signature|{{music|time|4|4}} time]] at a moderate [[tempo]] of 98 beats per minute. Grande's voice ranges from C{{Sharp}}<sub>4</sub> to G{{Sharp}}<sub>5</sub>.<ref>{{cite web|title = Ariana Grande \"Focus\" Sheet Music - Download & Print|url =http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0157236|publisher= Musicnotes|accessdate = July 23, 2017}}</ref> A [[Retro style|retro-styled]] song, \"Focus\" is based on a 1970s-inspired dance beat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2340923/ariana-grande-focus-song-teaser/|title= Ariana Grande's Latest 'Focus' Teaser Is The Most Revealing Yet|publisher= MTV News|first= Christina|last= Garibaldi|date= October 6, 2015|access-date= July 24, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304134303/http://www.mtv.com/news/2340923/ariana-grande-focus-song-teaser/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2015/10/30/ariana-grande-returns-with-new-single-focus/#7b52c5445386|title= Ariana Grande Returns With New Single 'Focus'|magazine= [[Forbes]]|first= Hugh|last= McIntyre|date= October 30, 2015|access-date= July 24, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304134442/https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2015/10/30/ariana-grande-returns-with-new-single-focus/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Idolator\">{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7610484/ariana-grande-tease-focus-single-listen-snippet|publisher= [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|title= Ariana Grande Continues To Tease \"Focus\" Single: Listen To A Snippet|date= October 30, 2015|accessdate= July 24, 2017|first= Mike|last= Wass}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7613370/pop-perspective-ariana-grande-focus-reviewed-rated-idolator-editors|title= Pop Perspective: Ariana Grande's \"Focus\" Reviewed And Rated By Idolator Editors|publisher= Idolator|date= October 30, 2015|access-date= July 24, 2017|first= Mike|last= Wass}}</ref> According to Ryan Reed of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', its instrumentation features \"stabbing big-band brass\" (with [[saxophone]], [[trumpet]] and a [[trombone]]), smooth [[synths]] and clanging [[percussion]] with synthesized handclaps and a [[cowbell (instrument)|cowbell]].<ref>{{cite magazine|title= Hear Ariana Grande's Brash, Brassy New Song 'Focus'|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/hear-ariana-grandes-brash-brassy-new-song-focus-20151030|magazine= Rolling Stone|first= Ryan|last= Reed|date= October 30, 2015|accessdate= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304135409/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/hear-ariana-grandes-brash-brassy-new-song-focus-20151030|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> The song's horn foundation has been compared to Grande's 2014 single, \"[[Problem (song)|Problem]]\" (featuring Australian rapper [[Iggy Azalea]]) from her album, ''[[My Everything (Ariana Grande album)|My Everything]]''.<ref name=\"Spin\">{{cite web|last1=Carley|first1=Brennan|title=Ariana Grande Returns With 'Focus,' the First Taste of New Album 'Moonlight'|url=http://www.spin.com/2015/10/ariana-grande-focus-music-video-moonlight/|website=Spin|accessdate=October 30, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304135515/https://www.spin.com/2015/10/ariana-grande-focus-music-video-moonlight/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Maslow|first1=Nick|title=Ariana Grande Turns Up the Heat in New 'Focus' Music Video|url=http://www.people.com/article/ariana-grande-focus-single-music-video|website=People|accessdate=October 30, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304142802/http://people.com/celebrity/ariana-grande-debuts-focus-single-and-music-video/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> In an''[[Entertainment Tonight]]''  interview, Grande acknowledged \"Focus{{\"'}} similarity to \"Problem\"; she thought the former would be the \"perfect transition record\" from her last album to her new album, because it sounds like \"Problem 2.0\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Schillaci|first1=Sophie|title=Ariana Grande Says Her Grandmother Inspired Her Platinum 'Focus' Makeover|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/175246_ariana_grande_says_her_grandmother_inspired_her_platinum_focus_makeover/|website=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|date=November 3, 2015|accessdate=November 24, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304143351/http://www.etonline.com/news/175246_ariana_grande_says_her_grandmother_inspired_her_platinum_focus_makeover|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nLyrically, Grande asks for attention and focus. According to [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'s Robbie Daw, the pre-chorus resembles the intro of [[KC and the Sunshine Band]]'s 1975 disco song, \"[[That's the Way (I Like It)]]\".<ref name=\"Idolator\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7613321/ariana-grande-focus-kc-and-the-sunshine-bands-thats-the-way-i-like-it-watch-video?andro=1|title= Ariana Grande's \"Focus\" Sounds Like KC And The Sunshine Band's \"That's The Way (I Like It)\": Watch The Video|publisher= Idolator|first= Robbie|last= Saw|date= October 30, 2015|access-date= March 3, 2018}}</ref> Marcus Floyd of Renowned for Sound wrote that in the second verse, Grande \"addresses her haters and insists that they address her realness\".<ref name=\"Renowned\"/> Its \"funky\" [[refrain|chorus]] consists of the repeated phrase, \"Focus on me\", sung by American actor [[Jamie Foxx]] in a bass voice.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2366855/ariana-grande-phone/?xrs=_s.fb_main|title=The Mystery Man on Ariana Grande's 'Focus' Has Been Revealed|publisher= MTV news| date=October 31, 2015|accessdate=October 31, 2015|first= Sasha|last= Geffen|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304143520/http://www.mtv.com/news/2366855/ariana-grande-phone/?xrs=_s.fb_main|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> Grande explained the hook:\n\n<blockquote>When I say, \"Focus on me\", I'm not asking to be the center of attention. I'm not asking you to focus on my face or my clothes or my body or my singing voice. By \"focus on me\", I literally mean focus on me. Focus on what I'm all about and what I believe in. The more we focus on each other as people and not on what we look like, what we're wearing, our gender, our hairstyle, our sexuality, the color of our skin. But focus on each other on a soul level. The more we realize how much we have in common, the more we listen to each other, the more one we become.<ref name=\"MTV1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2345735/ariana-grande-focus-meaning/|title= Ariana Grande's 'Focus' Is A Lot More Spiritual Than You May Think|publisher= MTV News|first= Amanda|last= Bell|date= October 9, 2017|accessdate=July 23, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304143821/http://www.mtv.com/news/2345735/ariana-grande-focus-meaning/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n==Critical reception==\nAmy Davison from [[Digital Spy]] praised \"Focus{{\"'}} \"sax-driven\" beat;<ref name=\"digitalspy\">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/music-videos/news/a676455/ariana-grandes-new-single-focus-has-arrived-with-a-music-video-in-tow/|title= Ariana Grande's new single 'Focus' has arrived with a music video in tow|website= [[Digital Spy]]|first= Amy|last= Davidson|date= October 30, 2017|access-date= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304145833/http://www.digitalspy.com/music/music-videos/news/a676455/ariana-grandes-new-single-focus-has-arrived-with-a-music-video-in-tow/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> ''[[The Verge]]''{{'s}} Kaitlyn Tiffany called Grande a \"massively talented vocalist\", and \"Focus\" a \"very pleasant\" listen.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2015/10/30/9646876/ariana-grande-focus-music-video-samsung-galaxy-note-5|title=Ariana Grande and the Galaxy Note 5 just dropped a new music video|work=[[The Verge]]|first=Kaitlyn|last=Tiffany|date=October 30, 2015|accessdate=October 31, 2015|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20151105140858/http://www.theverge.com/2015/10/30/9646876/ariana-grande-focus-music-video-samsung-galaxy-note-5|archivedate=November 5, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]''{{'}}s Nolan Feeney noted that although it was similar to \"Problem\", it may not have been a poor single decision.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://time.com/4094111/ariana-grande-focus/|title=Watch the Video for Ariana Grande's New Single 'Focus'|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=October 30, 2015|accessdate=October 31, 2015|first= Nolan|last= Freeney|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304150043/http://time.com/4094111/ariana-grande-focus/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> On Renowned for Sound, Marcus Floyd called \"Focus\" predictably \"catchy and attention grabbing\"; the song ticks \"all the boxes of an effective lead single.\" Giving it four out of five stars, he wrote that \"Focus\" is one of Grande's \"stronger single releases\" to date but did not \"venture out\" of her \"comfort zone.\"<ref name=\"Renowned\">{{cite web|url=http://renownedforsound.com/index.php/single-review-ariana-grande-focus/|title= Single Review: Ariana Grande \u2013 'Focus'|publisher= Renowned for sound|first= Marcus|last= Floyd|date= November 3, 2015|access-date= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304150150/http://renownedforsound.com/index.php/single-review-ariana-grande-focus/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> Steven J. Horowitz of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' gave the song two-and-a-half out of five stars and wrote that Grande had never released a \"less-than-great\" single until \"Focus\", which he considered a \"weak\" rehash of \"Problem\".<ref>{{cite magazine |last1= Horowitz|first1= Steven|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/track-review/6753991/ariana-grande-grimes-miike-snow-chance-the-rapper-singles-review|title=Does Ariana Grande's 'Focus' Need Sharpening? Plus More of the Week's Best & Worst Singles|magazine=Billboard|date=November 6, 2015 | accessdate=November 6, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304150456/https://www.billboard.com/articles/review/track-review/6753991/ariana-grande-grimes-miike-snow-chance-the-rapper-singles-review|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn a negative review, a ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine writer called \"Focus\" the sixth-worst song of 2015, calling Grande\u2019s vocal \"dwarfed\" by \"too-big instrumentals\" as it had been on \"Problem\" and \"[[Break Free (Ariana Grande song)|Break Free]]\"; however, the latter two had a \"sustaining energy\" which \"Focus\" lacked. The singer needed a \"tightly constructed, elegant hit\" after her [[Ariana Grande#Public image|2015 doughnut controversy]], \"and this isn\u2019t it\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://time.com/4133060/top-10-worst-songs-2/|title=Worst Songs of 2015|magazine=Time|date= December 3, 2015|accessdate=January 14, 2016|author= Time Staff|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304150643/http://time.com/4133060/top-10-worst-songs-2/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> Although Brennan Carley of ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' called the song a \"catchy slow-burn\" and a \"horn heavy piece of retro-modern fusion\", Grande's vocals lacked  \"real excitement from a star who\u2019s got the restraint and skill to take her instrument places most other pop singers can't anymore.\" Carley criticized the song's \"male howling\" for \"[getting] grating quickly\" and making \"Focus\" too similar to \"Problem\".<ref name=\"Spin\"/>\n\n===Year-end lists===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Publication\n! Rank\n! List\n|-\n| ''[[Stereogum]]''\n| align=\"center\"| 42\n| The 50 Best Pop Songs Of 2015<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.stereogum.com/1848717/the-50-best-pop-songs-of-2015/franchises/2015-in-review/3/ |title=The 50 Best Pop Songs of 2015 |website=Stereogum |date=17 December 2015 |accessdate=18 September 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Commercial performance==\n\"Focus\" debuted at number seven on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] in the United States, selling 113,000 digital downloads in its first full week, becoming Grande's sixth top-ten single and fourth top-ten debut on the chart.<ref name=\"top10\">{{cite web|title=Adele's 'Hello' Tops Hot 100 for Second Week; Ariana Grande, Meghan Trainor Hit Top 10 |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6754159/adele-hello-hot-100-second-week|website=[[Billboard.com]]|author=Gary Trust|date=November 9, 2015 |accessdate=November 11, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304154230/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6754159/adele-hello-hot-100-second-week|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> It was her first solo top ten in the country, unaccompanied by another artist.<ref name=\"top10\"/> The song entered the [[Digital Songs]] chart at number five and was number 13 on the Streaming Songs chart, with 13.3 million domestic streams.<ref name=\"top10\"/> It fell to number 13 in its second week on the Hot 100, rebounding to number 12 in its third week following Grande's performance at the [[American Music Awards of 2015|2015 American Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100/2015-11-28 | title=Hot 100: The week of November 28, 2015 | publisher=Prometheus Global Media | work=Billboard | accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref> By April 2018, \"Focus\" sold over 544,000 digital downloads in the US and was certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]].<ref name=\"us_sales\"/> It debuted and peaked at number eight on the [[Canadian Hot 100]], Grande's fifth Canadian top-ten single.\n\nThe song debuted at number ten on the [[Official Singles Chart]] in the United Kingdom, Grande's third top ten after the number-one singles \"Problem\" and \"[[Bang Bang (Jessie J, Ariana Grande and Nicki Minaj song)|Bang Bang]]\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Myers|first1=Justin|title=Adele says Hello to another week at Number 1|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adele-says-hello-to-another-week-at-number-1__11291|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=November 6, 2015|access-date= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304154423/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adele-says-hello-to-another-week-at-number-1__11291/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> It peaked at number six in its third week, spending three weeks in the chart's top ten. \"Focus\" also reached the top ten in Australia, Austria, Greece, Italy, the Netherlands and Spain.<ref name=\"Australiacharts\"/><ref name=\"Austriacharts\"/><ref name=\"Greececharts\"/><ref name=\"Spaincharts\"/>\n\n==Music video==\n===Background and synopsis===\n[[File:Ariana Grande - Focus (Screenshot).png|thumb|right|alt= A screenshot from a music video showing the body of a woman as a silhouette over a dark circle with purple shades.|Screenshot from the \"Focus\" video; according to Nick Maslow of ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazine, Grande appears in a \"world of purple\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.people.com/article/ariana-grande-focus-single-music-video|title=Ariana Grande Turns Up the Heat in New 'Focus' Music Video|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]|first= Nick|last= Maslow|date= October 7, 2015|accessdate=November 14, 2015}}</ref>]]\n\n[[Hannah Lux Davis]], who directed \"Focus{{\"'}} music video (released on October 30, 2015), also directed the music videos for Grande's \"[[Love Me Harder]]\" and the singer's joint single, \"[[Bang Bang (Jessie J, Ariana Grande and Nicki Minaj song)|Bang Bang]]\".<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Ariana Grande Drops New Single 'Focus'|magazine=Billboard|author= Billboard Staff|date=October 30, 2015|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6746034/ariana-grande-single-focus|accessdate=October 30, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304165930/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6746034/ariana-grande-single-focus|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> The video [[Product placement|features]] the [[Samsung Galaxy Note 5]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/samsung-galaxy-note-5-ariana-grandes-latest-music-video-focus-flaunts-powerful-2168432|title=Samsung Galaxy Note 5: Ariana Grande's Latest Music Video 'Focus' Flaunts The Powerful Phablet|newspaper= [[International Business Times]]|first= Pavithra|last= Rathinavel|date= November 4, 2015|accessdate=November 10, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304170309/http://www.ibtimes.com/samsung-galaxy-note-5-ariana-grandes-latest-music-video-focus-flaunts-powerful-2168432|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nGrande then performs a choreographed routine with six backing dancers on a purple set. During the second verse, she smiles and poses in a square wearing a black mini dress and high [[Toni Basil]]-style boots. For the song's bridge, the singer (in a star-print leotard, photographed in black-and-white) lies on a neon-lit set, plays a trumpet and performs with her dancers.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2015/10/29/video-ariana-grande-focus/|title= Ariana Grande - 'Focus'|magazine= [[Rap-Up]]|date= October 29, 2015|access-date= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304170534/http://www.rap-up.com/2015/10/29/video-ariana-grande-focus/|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> The video ends with her right eye illuminated. ''[[Teen Vogue]]''{{'}}s Ella Cer\u00f3n noted its \"slightly throwback\" visuals, which match the song.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/ariana-grande-focus-music-video|title= Ariana France's \"Focus\" Is Finally Here \u2013 And It's the Perfect Song to Sing to Your Haters|magazine= [[Teen Vogue]]|first= Ella|last= Cer\u00f3n|date= October 30, 2015|access-date= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304170702/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/ariana-grande-focus-music-video|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Reception===\nSean Fitz-Gerald of [[New York (magazine)#Digital expansion and blogs|Vulture]] called the video's geometric look similar to the videos for [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]'s \"[[Hotline Bling]]\" (2015) and [[Lil Mama]]'s \"[[Lip Gloss]]\" (2007).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vulture.com/2015/10/ariana-grande-focus-music-video.html|title= Here's Ariana Grande's Very Purple 'Focus' Video|work= Vulture|first= Sean|last= Fitz-Gerald|date= October 30, 2015|access-date= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304172400/http://www.vulture.com/2015/10/ariana-grande-focus-music-video.html|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> ''Billboard''{{'}}s staff ranked the music video for \"Focus\" as Grande's seventh-best, describing it as \"out-of-this-world\" with \"star-emblazoned jumpsuits and neon wigs\"; they compared the clip's aesthetic to the [[List of Disney Channel original films|Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Zenon: Girl of the 21st Century (film)|Zenon: Girl of the 21st Century]]'' (1999) and Grande's dancing to [[Beyonc\u00e9]]'s in the video for \"[[Single Ladies (Put a Ring on It)]]\" (2008).<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7318712/ariana-grande-best-music-videos|title= Ariana Grande's 10 Best Music Videos|magazine= Billboard|author= Billboard Staff|date= April 1, 2016|access-date= March 3, 2018}}</ref> The music video has received over 850 million views on [[YouTube]], becoming her fifth most-viewed upload on the site.\n\n==Live performances==\nGrande performed \"Focus\" live for the first time on the Honda Stage at the [[iHeartRadio]] Theater in Los Angeles on October 30, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.iheart.com/features/iheartradio-live-9/articles/15/489531/ariana-grande-world-premiere-event-on-14063515/|title=Ariana Grande World Premiere Event On The Honda Stage at the iHeartRadio Theater LA|publisher=[[iHeartRadio]]|accessdate=November 28, 2015|date= October 30, 2015|first= Nicole|last= Mastrogiannis|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180303182313/https://news.iheart.com/features/iheartradio-live-9/articles/15/489531/ariana-grande-world-premiere-event-on-14063515/|archivedate= March 3, 2018}}</ref> She also performed the song at the [[American Music Awards of 2015|2015 American Music Awards]] on November 22, ranked by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' as the best performance of the night.<ref>{{cite web|title=AMAs 2015: All the Performances Ranked From Worst to Best |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/amas/6770330/amas-2015-performances-ranked|website=[[Billboard.com]]|author=Joe Lynch|date=November 22, 2015 |accessdate=November 24, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304175258/https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/amas/6770330/amas-2015-performances-ranked|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> According to Bruna Nessif of ''[[E!]]'', Grande brought some \"old Hollywood glamour\" to the performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/718259/2015-american-music-awards-all-of-the-best-worst-moments|title= 2015 American Music Awards: All of the Best & Worst Moments!|work= [[E!]]|first= Bruna|last= Nessif|date= November 22, 2015|access-date= March 3, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304175632/http://www.eonline.com/news/718259/2015-american-music-awards-all-of-the-best-worst-moments|archivedate= March 4, 2018}}</ref> Grande performed \"Focus\" and a cover of \u201dMerry Christmas (War is Over)\u201d on [[Disney Parks Christmas Day Parade|Disney's Christmas Day special]].<ref>{{cite magazine | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/6821617/ariana-grande-merry-christmas-war-is-over-focus-disney-christmas-parade-2015 | title=Ariana Grande Sings 'Merry Christmas (War is Over)' & 'Focus' on Disney's Christmas Day Special|magazine=Billboard|first= Ashley|last= Iasimone|date=December 27, 2015|accessdate=December 27, 2015}}{{dead link|date=January 2020|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=\"Di\"/> \n| title1 = Focus\n| note1 = \n| length1 = 3:31\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Japanese CD [[maxi single]]<ref name=\"JP-R\"/>\n| title1 = Focus\n| length1 = 3:31\n| title2 = Focus\n| note2 = {{small|[[karaoke]] version}}\n| length2 = 3:31\n| title3 = Extra\n| note3 = \"Message in Japanese from Ariana\"\n| length3 = 0:40\n}}\n\n== Release formats ==\nThe Japanese [[Maxi single|CD maxi single]] set includes:\n\n;Regular edition<ref name=\"JP-R\"/>\n* One discs {{small|([[CD single]])}}\n* A mini-calendar\n* A mini-poster\n\n;Deluxe and limited edition<ref name=\"JP-D\"/>\n* One discs {{small|(CD single)}}\n* A poster\n* An A7-sized notebook\n\n==Credits and personnel==\n'''Recording'''\n*Recorded at [[MXM Studios]], [[Los Angeles]], [[United States]] and [[Wolf Cousins Studios]], [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]]\n*Mixed at MixStar Studios, [[Virginia Beach, Virginia|Virginia Beach]], United States\n*Mastered at [[Sterling Sound]], [[New York City]], United States\n\n'''Management'''\n\n*All rights administered by MXM (administered by Kobalt), [[Wolf Cousins]] (STIM), [[Warner/Chappell Music|Warner Chappel Music Scand]]([[STIM]]), Universal Music Corp./GRANDARIMUSIC (ASCAP)\n\n'''Personnel'''\n{{col begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n*[[Ariana Grande]]&nbsp;\u2013 lead vocals, songwriter\n*[[Savan Kotecha]]&nbsp;\u2013 songwriter, background vocals\n*[[Max Martin]]&nbsp;\u2013 songwriter, producer, programming\n*[[Ilya Salmanzadeh]]&nbsp;\u2013 songwriter, producer, guitar, bass, keyboards, programming, background vocals\n*Jonas Thander&nbsp;\u2013 horn arrangement, saxophone\n*Steffan Findin&nbsp;\u2013 trombone\n*Stefan Persson&nbsp;\u2013 trumpet\n{{col-2}}\n*{{ill|Jonne Bentl\u00f6v|sv}}&nbsp;\u2013 trumpet\n*[[Carolina Liar|Peter Carlsson]]&nbsp;\u2013 percussion\n*Peter Svensson&nbsp;\u2013 bass\n*[[Jamie Foxx]]&nbsp;\u2013 uncredited vocals\n*Sam Holland&nbsp;\u2013 recording\n*Serban Ghenea&nbsp;\u2013 mixing\n*[[Tom Coyne (music engineer)|Tom Coyne]]&nbsp;\u2013 mastering\n*John Hanes&nbsp;- mixing assistant\n{{col end}}\n'''Photographer'''\n\n* Alfredo Flores\n\nCredits adapted from the liner notes of ''Focus (CD Single)''.<ref name=\"Notes\" />\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Chart (2015\u201316)\n! Peak <br> position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|10|artist=Ariana Grande|song=Focus|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 7, 2015|refname=\"Australiacharts\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|9|artist=Ariana Grande|song=Focus|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 11, 2015|refname=\"Austriacharts\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|14|artist=Ariana Grande|song=Focus|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 6, 2015}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|33|artist=Ariana Grande|song=Focus|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 6, 2015}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canada|8|artist=Ariana Grande|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 10, 2015}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Canada CHR/Top 40]] ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref>{{cite web|title=Chart Search|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5b0%5d=ss_chart_search_title%3A%22Focus%22&f%5b1%5d=itm_field_chart_id%3A1239&refine=1|publisher=[[Billboard charts|Billboard]] [[Canada CHR/Top 40]] for Ariana Grande|accessdate=January 2, 2016}}</ref>\n| 11\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Canada Hot AC]] ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref>{{cite web|title