warehouse.com/data/active/p/penn_state/1990-1994_yearly_results.php}}</ref> The team was coached by [[Joe Paterno]] and played its home games in [[Beaver Stadium]] in [[University Park, Pennsylvania]].\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 1991\n| poll = AP\n| timezone = Eastern\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = {{tooltip|August 28|Wednesday}}\n| w/l = w\n| neutral = y\n| rank = 7\n| opponent = [[1991 Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets football team|Georgia Tech]]\n| opprank = 8\n| gamename = [[Kickoff Classic]]\n| site_stadium = [[Giants Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[East Rutherford, New Jersey|East Rutherford, NJ]]\n| tv = [[Raycom Sports|Raycom]]\n| score = 34\u201322\n| attend = 77,409\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 7\n| w/l = w\n| rank = 5\n| opponent = [[1991 Cincinnati Bearcats football team|Cincinnati]]\n| site_stadium = [[Beaver Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[University Park, Pennsylvania|University Park, PA]]\n| tv = [[Prime Sports|Prime]]\n| score = 81\u20130\n| attend = 94,000\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 14\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| rank = 5\n| opponent = [[1991 USC Trojans football team|USC]]\n| site_stadium = [[Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum]]\n| site_cityst = [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, CA]]\n| tv = [[ESPN on ABC|ABC]]\n| score = 10\u201321\n| attend = 64,758\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 21\n| w/l = w\n| rank = 12\n| opponent = [[1991 BYU Cougars football team|BYU]]\n| site_stadium = Beaver Stadium\n| site_cityst = University Park, PA\n| tv = ABC\n| score = 33\u20137\n| attend = 96,304\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 28\n| w/l = w\n| rank = 10\n| opponent = [[1991 Boston College Eagles football team|Boston College]]\n| site_stadium = Beaver Stadium\n| site_cityst = University Park, PA\n| tv = \n| score = 28\u201321\n| attend = 95,927\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 5\n| w/l = w\n| away = y\n| rank = 12\n| opponent = [[1991 Temple Owls football team|Temple]]\n| site_stadium =