dia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |pages=517\u2013523 |year=2015 |last1=Peterson |first1=Roger L. |last2=Peterson |first2=Donald R. |last3=Abrams |first3=Jules C. |last4=Stricker |first4=George |last5=Ducheny |first5=Kelly |isbn=978-0-08-097087-5 }}\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1016/B978-0-08-097086-8.24011-7 |chapter=Cross-Cultural Psychology |title=International Encyclopedia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |pages=311\u2013317 |year=2015 |last1=Poortinga |first1=Ype H. |isbn=978-0-08-097087-5 }}\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1016/B978-0-08-097086-8.92009-9 |chapter=Developmental Behavioral Genetics and Education |title=International Encyclopedia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |pages=320\u2013325 |year=2015 |last1=Spinath |first1=Frank M. |last2=Spinath |first2=Birgit |last3=Borkenau |first3=Peter |isbn=978-0-08-097087-5 }}\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1016/B978-0-08-097086-8.03028-2 |chapter=Cognitive Psychology: History |title=International Encyclopedia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |pages=103\u2013109 |year=2015 |last1=Smith |first1=Edward E. |isbn=978-0-08-097087-5 }}\n* {{cite book |doi=10.1016/B978-0-08-097086-8.24079-8 |chapter=Political Psychology |title=International Encyclopedia of the Social & Behavioral Sciences |pages=427\u2013433 |year=2015 |last1=Staerkl\u00e9 |first1=Christian |isbn=978-0-08-097087-5 }}\n* Gelder, Mayou & Geddes (2005). Psychiatry. New York: Oxford University Press Inc.\n\n== External links ==\n<!--======================== {{No more links}} ============================\n    | PLEASE BE CAUTIOUS IN ADDING MORE LINKS TO THIS ARTICLE. Wikipedia  |\n    | is not a collection of links nor should it be used for advertising. |\n    |                                                                     |\n    | Excessive or inappropriate links WILL BE DELETED.         |\n    | See [[Wikipedia:External links]] & [[Wikipedia:Spam]] for details.  |\n    |                                                                     |\n    | If there are