g==\n* {{Cite book| title=Cancer Wardile Chiri | publisher=Mathrubhui Books | date=12 December 2013 | author=Innocent | page=127 | isbn=9788182661110| id= {{ASIN|8182659108|country=in}} }}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Innocent (actor)}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0409204|name=Innocent}}\n* [http://thatsmalayalam.oneindia.in/movie/index.html Movie Index]{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}\n* https://web.archive.org/web/20160304064620/http://en.msidb.org/displayProfile.php?category=actors&artist=Innocent&limit=318\n* [http://164.100.47.194/Loksabha/Members/MemberBioprofile.aspx?mpsno=4886 16th LS member from Kerala]\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Innocent}}\n[[Category:Indian male comedians]]\n[[Category:People from Irinjalakuda]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Kerala]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Kerala State Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:1940s births]]\n[[Category:People from Thrissur]]\n[[Category:Cancer survivors]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:16th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:Independent politicians in India]]\n[[Category:Indian actor-politicians]]\n[[Category:Thrissur municipal councillors]]\n[[Category:Malayalam comedians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Kerala politicians]]\n[[Category:Revolutionary Socialist Party (India) politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Chalakudy]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Thrissur]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Malayalam screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Malayalam playback singers]]\n[[Category:Malayalam film producers]]\n[[Category:Film producers from Kerala]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{BLP sources|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Innocent \n| image = Innocent (Actor) 2011.png\n| caption = \n| office =  [[Member of Parliament, Lok Sabha]] \n| term_start = 16 May 2014  \n| term_end = 23 May 2019\n| constituency = [[Chalakudy (Lok Sabha constituency)|Chalakudy]]\n| predecessor = [[K. P. Dhanapalan]]\n| successor = [[Benny Behanan]]\n| office2 = [[Municipal council|Municipal Councillor]] of [[Irinjalakuda]]\n| term_start2 = 1979\n| term_end2 = \n| birth_name = Innocent Vareed Thekkethala\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1948|3|4}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Members : Lok Sabha (Innocent)|url=http://164.100.47.194/Loksabha/Members/MemberBioprofile.aspx?mpsno=4886|website=loksabha.nic.in|publisher=[[Lok Sabha]]|accessdate=10 March 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Irinjalakuda]], [[Travancore-Cochin]] (present-day [[Kerala]]), India\n| spouse = {{Marriage|Alice|1976}}\n| children = 1\n| occupation = {{hlist|Actor|writer|politician}}\n| awards = \n}}\n\n'''Innocent Vareed Thekkethala''' (born 4 March 1948), better known [[Mononymous person|mononymously]] as '''Innocent''', is an Indian film actor and politician. He served as the Member of Parliament in the 16th Lok Sabha of India representing [[Chalakudy (Lok Sabha constituency)|Chalakudy constituency]]. He predominantly works in [[Malayalam cinema]] in addition to [[Bollywood]], English, [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]], and [[Kannada cinema|Kannada]] films, mostly in comedic roles. He has acted in more than 750 films and has won several awards, including three [[Kerala State Film Awards]].\n\nIn 1979, he was elected as the [[Municipal council|Municipal Councillor]] of [[Irinjalakuda]] municipality. Innocent won the [[2014 Lok Sabha elections]] from [[Chalakudy (Lok Sabha constituency)|Chalakudy Lok Sabha constituency]] as an [[Independent politician|independent candidate]] supported by the [[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|Left Democratic Front]] (LDF).<ref name=LDFCandidate>{{cite news | url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/politics/in-kerala-left-backs-independent-innocent/ | title=In Kerala, Left backs Independent Innocent | newspaper=[[The Indian Express]] | date=7 March 2014 | accessdate=11 July 2016 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160829044806/http://indianexpress.com/article/india/politics/in-kerala-left-backs-independent-innocent/ | archivedate=29 August 2016 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> Innocent served as the President of the [[Association of Malayalam Movie Artists]] (AMMA), a guild of Malayalam artists from 2003 to 2018. He has written books based on his memoirs, and columns in magazines and newspapers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mangalam.com/cinema/interviews/101403 |title=\u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d3f\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d07\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d38\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d4d\u200c |publisher=mangalam.com |accessdate=23 April 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313092809/http://www.mangalam.com/cinema/interviews/101403 |archivedate=13 March 2014 }}</ref><ref>[[Association of Malayalam Movie Artists]][http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/kerala/2017/jul/05/kerala-actor-mp-innocent-says-bad-actresses-may-share-the-bed-at-will-1624654.html][https://www.indiatoday.in/fyi/story/innocent-kerala-cpm-mp-sexist-remark-apology-1022581-2017-07-05][https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/innocent-apologises-for-actors-action/article19217250.ece][https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/actor-innocent-call-it-quits-amma-president-end-term-78802]</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nInnocent was born on 4 March 1948 to Vareed Thekkethala and Margareetha in [[Irinjalakuda]], [[Travancore-Cochin]] (present-day [[Kerala]]), India.<ref>{{cite web|title=Innocent|url=https://www.india.gov.in/my-government/indian-parliament/innocent|website=india.gov.in|publisher=[[Government of India]]|accessdate=10 March 2019}}</ref> He had his primary education from [[Little Flower Convent Higher Secondary School, Irinjalakuda]], [[Don Bosco Higher Secondary School, Irinjalakuda]], and Sree Sangameswara NSS School, Irinjalakuda. He studied till eighth grade and discontinued his studies as he could not cope with studying. Innocent went to Madras (then) for his acting career and worked there as a production executive and during that time he acted in a minor role in the movie ''Nellu'', which was one of his earlier  movies. He fell ill, and came to Davangere in the 1970s for treatment for Typhoid, where his cousins Varunny (known as George, studying medicine at JJM Medical College), Davis and his brother Sensilavose were running the Shamannur Match factory, at Davangere. Later, he was an active partner in the working of the factory. As Innocent was keen on the performance activities, he seized the opportunity to participate in Davangere, Kerala Samajam drama and received audience approval in entertainment events.\n\nHe left Davangere in 1974, set up a leather business, then a cycle renting business to make a living. He always had constant conflict with his father, Vareed, because he thought Innocent would be a burden. Later, he joined politics and became Municipal councilor of Irinjalakuda.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinidiary.com/people.php?pigsection=Actor&picata=1&no_of_displayed_rows=18&no_of_rows_page=10&sletter=|title=CINIDIARY - A Complete Online Malayalam Cinema News Portal|website=cinidiary.com|accessdate=9 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20150507174335/http://cinidiary.com/people.php?pigsection=Actor&picata=1&no_of_displayed_rows=18&no_of_rows_page=10&sletter=|archivedate=7 May 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Film career==\nInnocent's mannerisms and diction is unique in Malayalam cinema and he wildly caught the attention of the Malayalam audience. This made him almost a phenomenon in the Malayalam comedy scene, also making him a hot favourite for mimicry artistes. His popularity can be gauged from the fact that many frontline directors in Malayalam (like [[Priyadarshan]], [[Sathyan Anthikad|Satyan Anthikkad]], [[Fazil (director)|Fazil]] and [[Kamal (director)|Kamal]]) rarely make films without Innocent. He has proven his acting skills in serious and character roles in several films. He has been the president of [[Association of Malayalam Movie Artistes]] (AMMA) for 12 years. He has held the post for the last four consecutive terms.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manoramaonline.com/cgi-bin/MMOnline.dll/portal/ep/malayalamContentView.do?contentId=14600115&programId=1073752204&channelId=-1073750705&BV_ID=@@@&tabId=3 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20131213082544/http://www.manoramaonline.com/cgi-bin/MMOnline.dll/portal/ep/malayalamContentView.do?contentId=14600115&programId=1073752204&channelId=-1073750705&BV_ID=@@@&tabId=3 |url-status=dead |archive-date=13 December 2013 |title=Movies &#124; Interviews &#124; |publisher=Manorama Online |accessdate=23 April 2014}}</ref>\n\nInnocent entered the film industry in 1972 with the movie ''Nrityashala''. At first, he produced a few serious offbeat films, but he was not successful. In the long span of his career, Innocent has worked in more than 500 films in a variety of roles, mainly in [[Malayalam]]. He has also acted in a few [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] and [[Hindi cinema|Hindi]] films.\n\nInnocent played key comedy roles in superhits like ''[[Ramji Rao Speaking]]'', ''[[Mannar Mathai Speaking]]'', ''[[Kilukkam]]'', ''[[Godfather (1991 film)|Godfather]]'', ''[[Vietnam Colony]]'', ''[[Nadodikattu]]'' and ''[[Devaasuram]]''.\nInnocent has also excelled in character and villain roles such as ''[[Keli (film)|Keli]]'',''[[Kathodu Kathoram]]''.\n\nHe proved his skills in other serious roles with a touch of laughter in films such as ''[[Kabooliwala|Kabooliwaala]]'', ''[[Gajakesariyogam]]'', ''[[Mithunam (1993 film)|Mithunam]]'', ''[[Mazhavilkavadi]]'', ''[[Manassinakkare]]'', ''[[Thuruppugulan (2006 film)|Thuruppugulan]]'', ''[[Rasathanthram]]'', and ''[[Mahasamudram]]''. His effort, along with that of the superstars who starred in these films, played an important role in their success. His pairing with [[K. P. A. C. Lalitha]] was highly successful in movies such as ''[[Ponmuttayidunna Tharavu|Ponn Muttayidunna Tharavu]]'', ''[[My Dear Muthachan|My Dear Muthachchan]]'', ''[[Godfather (1991 film)|Godfather]]'' and ''[[Manichitrathazhu]]''.\n\nInnocent is one of the most imitated actors of [[Malayalam cinema]] and [[mimicry]] artists have brought him closer to women and children among his fans. The best example of this can be seen in the widely popular Maveli ([[Mahabali]]) comedy cassettes which are brought out by various mimicry groups annually in association with the [[Onam]] festival of [[Kerala]] in the past few years. These cassettes satirise [[Mahabali]], a benevolent King in Kerala's mythology, who is supposed to visit his subjects in [[Kerala]] every lunar year on the day of [[Onam]]. These cassettes tend to portray Maveli ([[Mahabali]]) as a comic King who gets into all sort of troubles \u2013 the script makes use of many contemporary issues in [[Kerala]] \u2013 on his annual arrival in Kerala. Mimicry artistes uses Innocent's voice to represent Maveli and all his mannerisms and idiosyncrasies in speech are deftly mimicked to generate laughter in the audience.\n\nInnocent's participation in stage shows guarantees him a leading role as an anchor or performer. His [[Katha (storytelling format)|Kathaprasangam]] (oratory combined with poetry) ''Olayaal Menjoru'' is one of the regulars in Gulf stage shows.\n\nInnocent has published his memoirs: ''Njan Innocent''. He has published three other books: ''Mazha Kannadi'' (collection of short stories), ''Chirrikku Pinnil'' (an autobiography) and ''Cancer Wardile Chiri'' (Laughter in the Cancer Ward), an account of his experiences while undergoing treatment for throat cancer.<ref name=\"Cancer Wardile Chiri\">{{Cite book| title=Cancer Wardile Chiri | publisher=Mathrubhui Books | date=12 December 2013 | author=Innocent | page=127 | isbn=9788182661110| id= {{ASIN|8182659108|country=in}} }}</ref> Innocent also writes columns in magazines and newspapers.\n\n==Politics==\nInnocent was the Thrissur District Secretary of the [[Revolutionary Socialist Party (India)|Revolutionary Socialist Party]] during the 1970s. He had contested in the Irinjalakkuda municipal council elections as [[Revolutionary Socialist Party (India)|Revolutionary Socialist Party]]-backed candidate in 1979 and had won that election.<ref name=LDFCandidate /> He was rumoured to be a [[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|Left Democratic Front]] (LDF)-supported independent candidate from the [[Irinjalakkuda]] assembly constituency in the [[2006 Kerala Legislative Assembly election]]s but this did not happen.<ref name=sathyanaward>{{cite web|url=http://cinema4utv.blogspot.com/2007/11/awarded-for-talent-innocent.html|title=Innocent|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20080323055405/http://cinema4utv.blogspot.com/2007/11/awarded-for-talent-innocent.html|archivedate=23 March 2008|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Innocent won the [[2014 Lok Sabha elections]] from [[Chalakudy (Lok Sabha constituency)|Chalakudy Lok Sabha constituency]] in [[Thrissur district]] as an independent candidate supported by the LDF.<ref name=LDFCandidate />\n\nHe lost in the Lok sabha elections 2019 with a margin of 132274 votes to UDF candidate [[Benny Behanan]].\n\n==Personal life==\nHe married Alice on September 26, 1976 and had a son Sonnet. Sonnet is married, with two children, Innocent Jr and Anna. Jr. Innocent has acted in a documentary as Innocent in childhood.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mangalam Varika 15 Oct 2012|url=http://www.mangalamvarika.com/index.php/en/home/index/54/39|publisher=mangalamvarika.com|accessdate=30 October 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140329002110/http://www.mangalamvarika.com/index.php/en/home/index/54/39|archivedate=29 March 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Both Innocent and his wife are cancer survivors.\n\n==Awards==\n;[[Kerala State Film Awards]]\n* 1989 \u2013 [[Kerala State Film Award for Second Best Actor|Second Best Actor]] \u2013 Mazhavil Kavadi\n* 1981 \u2013 [[Kerala State Film Award for Second Best Film|Second Best Film]] (Producer) \u2013 Vida Parayum Munpe\n* 1982 \u2013 [[Kerala State Film Award for Second Best Film|Second Best Film]] (Producer) \u2013 Ormakkayi\n\n;Kerala State Film Critics Award\n* 2009 \u2013 Best Actor \u2013 Patham Nilayile Theevandi\n\n;[[Asianet Film Award]]\n* 2001 \u2013 [[Asianet Film Awards#Best Supporting Actor|Supporting Actor Award]] \u2013 [[Ravanaprabhu]]\n* 2004 \u2013 Supporting Actor Award \u2013 [[Vesham]]\n* 2006 \u2013 [[Asianet Film Award#Best Actor in a Comic Role|Best Actor in a Comic Role]] \u2013 [[Rasathanthram]], Yes Your Honour\n* 2008 \u2013 Supporting Actor Award \u2013 [[Innathe Chintha Vishayam]]\n* 2013 \u2013 Lifetime Achievement Award<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metromatinee.com/news-articles/16th-ujala-asianet-film-awards-2014-winners-list-7548 |title=16th Ujala Asianet Film Awards 2014 \u2013 Winners List |publisher=Metromatinee.com |date=11 January 2014 |accessdate=23 April 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140517014018/http://www.metromatinee.com/news-articles/16th-ujala-asianet-film-awards-2014-winners-list-7548 |archivedate=17 May 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n;Other awards\n* 2007 \u2013 [[Sathyanesan Nadar|Sathyan]] Award<ref name=sathyanaward />\n* 2008 \u2013 Annual Malayalam Movie Award (Dubai) for Outstanding Performance\n* 2013 \u2013 TTK Prestige-Vanitha Film Awards \u2013 Lifetime Achievement Award\n* 2019 \u2013He is Distributing Awards Realtors Investors Summit<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kerala9.com/news-category/news/movie-news/ttk-prestige-vanitha-film-awards-shobhana-prithviraj-win-best-actor-actress-awards |title=TTK Prestige-Vanitha Film Awards: Shobhana, Prithviraj win best actor, actress awards |publisher=Kerala9.com |date=20 January 2014 |accessdate=23 April 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140307082405/http://kerala9.com/news-category/news/movie-news/ttk-prestige-vanitha-film-awards-shobhana-prithviraj-win-best-actor-actress-awards |archivedate=7 March 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Partial Filmography==\n\n===As actor===\n;Malayalam films\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!No.\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title \n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" | Notes\n|-\n|1\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2019\n|[[Ganagandharvan|''Gaanagandharvan'']]\n|Appukutta Panicker\n|\n|-\n|2\n|''[[Lonappante Mamodeesa]]'' ||School Teacher\n|Guest Appearance\n|-\n|3\n|''[[Irupathiyonnaam Noottaandu]]''||Bishop\n|\n|-\n|4\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2018 || ''[[Odiyan]]'' || Gopi Mash\n|\n|-\n|5\n| ''[[Suvarna Purushan]]'' || Rappayi \n|\n|-\n|6\n| ''[[Njan Marykutty]]'' ||Priest\n|\n|-\n|7\n| ''[[Kuttanadan Marpappa]]'' ||  \nUmmachan\n|\n|-\n|8\n|rowspan=\"4\" | 2017 || ''[[Aana Alaralodalaral]]'' || Pathrose  \n|\n|-\n|9\n| ''GandhiNagaril Unniyarcha'' ||  \n|\n|-\n|10\n| ''[[Pullikkaran Staraa]]'' || Omanakshan Pillai \n|\n|-\n|11\n| ''[[Jomonte Suvisheshangal]]'' || Palodan \n|\n|-\n|12\n|rowspan=\"1\" | 2016 || ''[[Swarna Kaduva]]'' ||Lolappan \n|\n|-\n|13\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2015 || ''[[Kanal (2015 film)|Kanal]]'' || Natesan\n|\n|-\n|14\n| ''[[Urumbukal Urangarilla]]'' || Madhavettan\n|\n|-\n|15\n| ''[[Ennum Eppozhum]]'' || Kariyachan\n|\n|-\n|16\n| rowspan=\"8\" | 2014 || ''Thomson Villa'' || Priest\n|\n|-\n|17\n| ''[[Aamayum Muyalum]]'' || Nallavan\n|\n|-\n|18\n| ''[[Nagara Varidhi Naduvil Njan]]'' ||Davis\n|\n|-\n|19\n| ''[[Njangalude Veettile Athidhikal]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|20\n| ''[[Bhaiyya Bhaiyya]]'' ||Kochuveettil Chacko\n|\n|-\n|21\n| ''[[Polytechnic (film)|Polytechnic]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|22\n| ''Malayalakkara Residency'' ||\n|\n|-\n|23\n| ''[[Mannar Mathai Speaking 2]]'' || Mannar Mathai\n|\n|-\n|24\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2013 || ''[[Philips and the Monkey Pen]]'' || God\n|\n|-\n|25\n| ''[[Geethaanjali]]'' || Thankappan\n|\n|-\n|26\n| ''[[Punyalan Agarbattis]]'' || John Thakkolkaran\n|\n|-\n|27\n| ''[[Oru Indian Pranayakatha]]'' || Uthup Vallikkadan\n|\n|-\n|28\n| rowspan=\"10\" | 2012 || ''[[Puthiya Theerangal]]'' || Father Michael\n|\n|-\n|29\n| ''[[Husbands in Goa]]'' || Nadar (TTE)\n|\n|-\n|30\n| ''[[Arike]]'' || Kalpana's father\n|\n|-\n|31\n| ''[[Bhoopadathil Illatha Oridam]]'' || Police Officer\n|\n|-\n|32\n| ''Perinoru Makan'' || Harischandran\n|\n|-\n|33\n| ''[[Mullassery Riyas C S badrun P. O.]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|34\n| ''[[Kaashh]]'' || Devasiya\n|\n|-\n|35\n| ''[[Chattakkari (2012 film)|Chattakaari]]'' || Morris\n|\n|-\n|36\n| ''[[Naughty Professor]]'' || Mulavarikkal Francis\n|\n|-\n|37\n| ''[[Doctor Innocent aanu]]'' || Doctor Bargavan Pillai\n|\n|-\n|38\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2011 || ''[[Snehaveedu]]'' || Mathai\n|\n|-\n|39\n| ''[[Living Together (film)|Living Together]]'' || Krishnaprasad Kartha\n|\n|-\n|40\n| ''[[Doctor Love (film)|Doctor Love]]'' || Sathyasheelan\n|\n|-\n|41\n| ''[[Pachuvum Kovalanum]]'' || Bhadranpillai\n|\n|-\n|42\n| ''[[Oru Marubhoomikkadha]]'' || Mathayi\n|\n|-\n|43\n| ''[[Swapna Sanchari]]'' || Achuthan Nair\n|\n|-\n|44\n| rowspan=\"10\" | 2010 || ''[[Marykkundoru Kunjaadu]]'' || Ittichan Muthalali\n|\n|-\n|45\n| ''[[Cocktail (2010 film)|Cocktail]]'' || Kalyan Krishnan\n|\n|-\n|46\n| ''[[Oridathoru Postman]]'' || Gangadharan\n|\n|-\n|47\n| ''[[Pappy Appacha]]'' || Nirappel Mathai\n|\n|-\n|48\n| ''[[Cheriya Kallanum Valiya Policum]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|49\n| ''[[Again Kasargod Khader Bhai]]'' || Father Francis Tharakan\n|\n|-\n|50\n| ''[[Kanyakumari Express (film)|Kanyakumari Express]]'' || Minister\n|\n|-\n|51\n| ''[[Aagathan]]'' || Lawrence\n|\n|-\n|52\n| ''[[Kadha Thudarunnu]]'' || Lasar\n|\n|-\n|53\n| ''[[Pranchiyettan & the Saint]]'' || Vasu Menon\n|\n|-\n|54\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2009 || ''[[Patham Nilayile Theevandi]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|55\n| ''[[Ee Pattanathil Bhootham]]'' \n|Krishnan\n|\n|-\n|56\n| ''[[Bhagyadevatha]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|57\n| ''[[Duplicate (2009 film)]]'' || P Suresh\n|\n|-\n|58\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2008 || ''[[Twenty:20 (film)|Twenty:20]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|59\n| ''[[Veruthe Oru Bharya]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|60\n| ''[[Madampi]]'' ||\nKarayogam President\n|\n|-\n|61\n| '' [[Jubilee (2008 film)|Jubilee]]'' || Thomas Kora\n|\n|-\n|62\n| ''[[Innathe Chintha Vishayam]]'' || Emmanuel\n|\n|-\n|63\n| ''[[Calcutta News]]'' || Kerala samajam president\n|\n|-\n|64\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2007 || ''[[Katha Parayumbol]]'' || Eepachan Muthalali\n|\n|-\n|65\n| ''[[Ali Bhai]]'' || Khalid Ahemmed Sayivu\n|\n|-\n|66\n| ''[[Mission 90 Days]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|67\n| ''[[Inspector Garud (film)|Inspector Garud]]'' || Raghavan\n|\n|-\n|68\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2006 || ''[[Baba Kalyani (film)|Baba Kalyani]]'' || Car Dealer\n|\n|-\n|69\n| ''[[Mahasamudram]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|70\n| ''[[Thuruppugulan (2006 film)|Thuruppu Gulan]]'' || Kochu Thoma\n|\n|-\n|71\n| ''[[Kilukkam Kilukilukkam]]'' || Kittunni\n|\n|-\n|72\n| ''[[Rasathanthram]]'' || Manikandan Aashari\n|\n|-\n|73\n| ''[[Malamaal Weekly]]'' || Joseph Anthony Fernandes\n|\n|-\n|74\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2005 || ''[[Bus Conductor (2005 film)|Bus Conductor]]'' ||Majeed\n|\n|-\n|75\n| ''[[Thanmathra]]'' || Sukumaran Nair\n|\n|-\n|76\n| ''[[Naran (film)|Naran]]'' || Kelappan\n|\n|-\n|77\n| ''[[Udayon]]'' || Rarichan\n|\n|-\n|78\n| ''[[Thaskaraveeran (2005 film)|Thaskara Veeran]]'' || Eappachan\n|\n|-\n|79\n| ''[[Achuvinte Amma]]'' || Paulose\n|\n|-\n|80\n| rowspan=\"10\" | 2004 || ''[[Nothing but Life|Made in USA]]'' || Prof. Ponnachan PHD\n|\n|-\n|81\n| ''[[Vesham]]'' || Pappan\n|\n|-\n|82\n| ''[[Maampazhakkaalam]]'' || Chandran's Uncle\n|\n|-\n|83\n| ''[[Greetings (2004 film)|Greetings]]'' || Aravindakshan Nair\n|\n|-\n|84\n| ''[[Kaazhcha]]'' || Fr. Kuriakose\n|\n|-\n|85\n| ''Chitrakoodam'' || Balan\n|\n|-\n|86\n| ''[[Vettam]]'' || K. T. Mathew\n|\n|-\n|87\n| ''[[Wanted (2004 film)|Wanted]]'' || Unni's Uncle\n|\n|-\n|88\n| ''[[Vamanapuram Bus Route]]'' || Chandran Pillai\n|\n|-\n|89\n| ''Thalamelam'' || Kunjukuttan Thampuran\n|\n|-\n|90\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2003 || ''[[Manassinakkare]]'' || Chacko Mappila\n|\n|-\n|91\n| ''[[Ammakilikkoodu]]'' || Eradi\n|\n|-\n|92\n| ''[[Pattalam (Malayalam film)|Pattalam]]'' || Sivasankaran Nair\n|\n|-\n|93\n| ''[[Balettan]]'' || Achumama\n|\n|-\n|94\n| ''[[Vellithira (2003 film)|Vellithira]]'' || Ittiyavira\n|\n|-\n|95\n| ''[[Chronic Bachelor]]'' || Kuruvilla\n|\n|-\n|96\n| rowspan=\"8\" | 2002 || ''[[Kalyanaraman (2002 film)|Kalyanaraman]]'' || Ponjikkara Kesavan\n|\n|-\n|97\n| ''[[Nammal]]'' || Shanmughan\n|\n|-\n|98\n| ''[[Nandanam (film)|Nandanam]]'' || Kesavan Nair\n|\n|-\n|99\n| ''[[Yathrakarude Sradhakku]]'' || Paul\n|\n|-\n|100\n| ''Jagathi Jagathish in Town'' || Neelakandan\n|\n|-\n|101\n| ''[[Phantom (2002 film)|Phantom]]'' || The Priest\n|\n|-\n|102\n| ''Savithriyute Aranjanam'' || Ravunni\n|\n|-\n|103\n| ''Snehithan'' || Devassy\n|\n|-\n|104\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2001 || ''[[Ishtam (2001 Malayalam film)|Ishtam]]'' || Narayanan\n|\n|-\n|105\n| ''[[Ravanaprabhu]]'' || Warrier\n|\n|-\n|106\n| ''Uthaman'' || Chacko Cherian\n|\n|-\n|107\n| ''[[Narendran Makan Jayakanthan Vaka]]'' || Johnny Vellikala\n|\n|-\n|108\n| ''[[Kakkakuyil]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|109\n| ''[[Nakshathragal Parayathirunnathu]]'' || Govinda Kamath\n|\n|-\n|110\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2000 || ''[[Kochu Kochu Santhoshangal]]'' || Jose\n|\n|-\n|111\n| ''[[Life Is Beautiful (2000 film)|Life Is Beautiful]]'' || Nambiar\n|\n|-\n|112\n| ''Mr. Butler'' || Captain K.G.Nair\n|\n|-\n|113\n| ''[[Valliettan]]'' || Ramankutty Kaimal\n|\n|-\n|114\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 1999 || ''[[Aakasha Ganga]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|115\n| ''[[Chandranudikkunna Dikhil]]'' ||\n|\n|-\n|116\